>Be coming home from a month straight of adventurer shenanigans

>You don't want to save the world. >You just want to make boatloads of phat l00t, sweep stacks of cash money, and swing big fuckoff swords but the universe just won't let you

>No...

>It bounds into the air excitedly, thumping down right onto your gut and knocking the wind out of you.
>"Anon! Oh my gosh Anon! Hi, hi!"
>The little creature starts dancing excitedly atop you, it's hind paws doing enthusiastic little tippy-taps.
>"Betcha can't guess who it is, can you Nonners?~" it trills in a sing song voice and clearly affected accent.
>You can tell just from her obnoxiously large, glowing bright green eyes exactly who it is.
>"Hello Meela..." You groan, pinching the bridge of your nose. "How was your trip to Fantasy New York?"
>Probably shouldn't have said that. Give this little fennec fox...thing an inch and she'll take a mile.
>Especially if it means she gets to talk to you.
>*Gasp!* "Oh my gosh, Nonny you remembered!~ Oh, you sweetheart you!~" She cries, bouncing on you, again, before flopping down on top of you for some involuntary hugging time. "You're such a good h--f-friend!~"
>She was totally going to say husband.
>And so the torment begins.
>The yammering...it just doesn't stop.
